==German==
===Etymology===
Old High German ''[[in]]'' ''[[ebanī]]''

===Preposition===
'''neben'''

# [[near]], [[near to]], [[next to]]
#: ''Der Sofa geht neben den Tisch'' : The sofa goes next to the table.
#: ''Der Sofa steht neben dem Tisch'' : The sofa stays next to the table.
Note: The preposition "neben" is used with accusative case if the verb shows movement from one place to another, whereas it is used with dative case if the verb shows location.

